* search: match numeric (dec or hex) character codes or numeric entities
* search: match HTML named entities
* display JS surrogate pair chars for > xFFFF
* display encoded bytes as hex (UTF-8, UTF-16L/E, UTF-32L/E)
* accept encoded hex bytes
* display search results in a persistent, scrolling list
* make next/prev buttons repeat when held down
* support scroll wheel in char-input box
* enumerate installed fonts for autocomplete
* save font selection in cookie

* Anomalous displays:
  * Search for: link vs /link/
  * Hangul Syllable AC00, First displayed, but rest not because no descriptions
  * Combining chars (eg: 0300) not visible in chart
